Ah, this lovely holy month of Ramadan is slowly coming to an end. Wish&nbsp;it could have lasted longer, but&nbsp;it was fun while it lasted.&nbsp;;) 
Yesterday,&nbsp;before sehri, my&nbsp;brother was constantly&nbsp;on his laptop, watching his shows, listening to music, reading reviews. I got annoyed.&nbsp;So when I finally asked his permission to borrow the laptop to watch one of my dramas (as I haven't watched anything since coming to Karachi), he naturally declined and taunted me. But then I thought to myself, why waste my energy harbouring&nbsp;anger and&nbsp;useless animosities. So I decided to read the Q'uran&nbsp;with english translation until Sehri. Ahh, it was so refreshing and peaceful, much better than devouring on materialistic stuff and being oblivious to the suffering thats going on here (im referring to my brother).&nbsp; 

Then today, I went to&nbsp;the local Masjid near my&nbsp;Dadi's house and prayed the whole Tarawi. It&nbsp;felt good.&nbsp; 
Eid is gonna be&nbsp;awesome, and then&nbsp;all&nbsp;my relatives will go for a picnic at the beach!!! Im totally pumped! Can't wait! :D :D :D&nbsp;

*WARNING: BIG FANGIRL RANT BELOW ON THE 'NARUTO&nbsp;MANGA'&nbsp;WITH SPOILERS UNTIL CHAPTER 423* PROCEED WITH CAUTION. YOU HAVE BEEN WARNED!: 

Realised I needed to catch up on the 'Naruto' manga, but oh...god....first, the SHOCKING&nbsp;revelation of Itachi (sasuke's brother) and how he in fact was *gasp*&nbsp;NOT a bad guy!!!! omg, its sooo darn tragic!!!! i don't think ive ever cried so much for&nbsp;someone who I really hated&nbsp;and&nbsp;was decieved to think he was the bad guy the WHOLE time until his death, but then later on knowing that he WASN'T!!!! &gt;__&lt; oh gosh, cannot decribe, you would&nbsp;just need to read it...&nbsp;SASUKE..you're such an IDIOT!!!! &gt;__&lt; 

BUT!! thats not even&nbsp;HALF of it!&nbsp;Then Jiraiya-sama!!!!! oh gosh another victim! and THEN.....T-T-THENN....K-K-Kakashi-senseiiii!!!!!!!!!!!!!! OH&nbsp;MY&nbsp;GOD!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! WHYYY&nbsp;OH&nbsp;WHYYYY DID&nbsp;HE&nbsp;HAVE&nbsp;TO&nbsp;DIE!!!!!! NOOOOO!!!! ANYONE BUT HIM!!!! I WANT HIM BACK, YOU HEAR ME???!!!! TT_________TT (BOTH OF THEM WERE KILLED BY PAIN!!!! i mean the villain's name is 'PAIN' not the&nbsp;feeling&nbsp;'pain'...) 
&nbsp; 
i refuse to believe it, cos it was such an anticlimatic and unconventional way to&nbsp;kill off such an IMPORTANT character!!! 
&nbsp;I was shocked to the CORE and my lacrimal glands just WON'T STOP secreting tears!!! i've been&nbsp;CRYING 'non-stop' after that chapter, thinking that it can't be possible!!!! but with each chapter, its just slowly becoming clearer and it sorta starting to sink in... but luckily right now im trying to avoid thinking about it by focusing and admiring Naruto's new 'SAGE MODE' and all his fancy NEW ninja techniques!!! it's JUST AMAZING to see how much he's matured!!!!! how brilliantly tactful he's become now. 

aughh, it really seems that an 'apocalypse' has erupted now, and that the manga is nearing it's end soon.&nbsp; 
damn, this manga is&nbsp;NOT for the faint-hearted!!!!!!!!!&nbsp; 
I&nbsp;have&nbsp;an extremely 'fragile' heart,&nbsp;so I don't think I can endure any more deaths, you hear me, Kishimoto-san???!!!! 

naruto...please kill 'pain' for me (lol, how ironic) and avenge&nbsp;Kakashi-sensei's death!&nbsp;im counting on you to save me from my grief and sorrow! 
&nbsp;
